			<div id="post-76" class="cf post-76 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-uncategorized">

	<h2>
		<span class="post-format"></span>
		<a href="http://werblog.com/2002/06/from-david-isenbergs-smart-letter/" title="From David Isenberg&#039;s SMART Letter:" rel="bookmark">From David Isenberg&#039;s SMART Letter:</a>
		
	</h2>

	
	
	<div class="post-bodycopy cf">
	
		<div class="post-date">		
			<p class="post-month">Jun</p>
			<p class="post-day">29</p>
			<p class="post-year">2002</p>				
		</div>

		From David Isenberg&#8217;s SMART Letter: &#8220;Motorola has just launched a wireless, unlicensed (5GHz) last-mile product line named Canopy that delivers up to 10 megabits per second per subscriber, for up to 1200 subscribers per access point, for a one-time cost that asymptotes at around $500 list.&#8221;
		
	</div>

	<div class="post-footer">
		<a class="post-readmore" href="http://werblog.com/2002/06/from-david-isenbergs-smart-letter/" title="From David Isenberg&#039;s SMART Letter:">
